XVII. PUBLIUS CORNELIUS SCIPIO AFRICANUS.

Pnge 34. 1. Psrbllue Cornelius Scipio: the Scipios were apatrician family of the Cornelian gens. This family produced some of the greatest men of Rome, all of whom were strong partisans of the aristocratic faction. The family tomb of the Scipios was discovered in 1780 near the Porta Capena, and is one of the most interesting remains of the Republic.
